    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "China's claim is based on a century-old doctrine known as the \"Nine-Dash Line,\" which they assert grants them sovereignty over the entire South China Sea, a position that ignores the specific territorial claims of Vietnam, the Philippines, and Malaysia. While they argue these nations have no legal standing to challenge their historical rights, the international community overwhelmingly recognizes that these islands are not China's exclusive property. This fundamental disagreement over sovereignty is precisely why the situation remains so volatile; China's refusal to compromise on its historical narrative forces other nations to choose between respecting their own territorial integrity or accepting Chinese dominance.",
