      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"international community\" consensus is not a monolith, but the 2016 Permanent Court of Arbitration (PCA) ruling is the only legally binding precedent that definitively rejects China's \"Nine-Dash Line\" claims, and it is the standard used by the vast majority of nations and international courts. While China has consistently refused to accept the ruling, labeling it invalid due to procedural issues, this refusal does not negate the legal reality established by the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea, which most nations have ratified. Ultimately, the situation is a clash between China's unilateral assertion of historical rights and the established international legal order, where the PCA ruling represents the definitive legal truth, even if China's political power allows them to ignore it.",
      "source": "target",
